ted to hidden tags using custom tags, and programmers don't need to manually write hidden tags in JSP. There's also an image reference and a lead-in to an example using a survey application.\n\nNow moving to the next sections, I'm seeing guidance on when to use window scope versus session scope. The key point is that window scope should be the default choice, with session scope only used when data needs to be shared across windows. For data that doesn't require cross-window sharing, window scope is preferred and covers most use cases. The final section appears to contain reference links for additional details. I'm working through whether to preserve the referral section. The introductory sentence is clearly Layer C material that should be removed, but the cross-reference links themselves point to specific resources that are worth keeping for navigation. Since this is a guide-type document where I should lean toward preserving content, I'll include those links while dropping the referral framing. Now I'm ready to write out the sections.\n\nFor the first section on operation flow, there's a sequence diagram showing how window scope manages data across multiple screens using hidden tags instead of session scope. I'll provide a text description of this flow rather than relying solely on the image.\n\nFor the second section, I'm outlining the key distinction: window scope is the default approach, but session scope becomes necessary when data needs to be shared across different windows—like a shopping cart that must persist across multiple browser windows.\n\nThe final section references related documentation on variable scope usage and window scope best practices. ウィンドウスコープに格納された変数はカスタムタグで自動的にhiddenタグに変換されるため、プログラマが手動で記述する必要がない。hiddenで引き継がれるデータはウィンドウ内のHTMLに限定されるので、複数リクエスト間でのデータ共有が他のウィンドウやタブに影響を与えずに実現される。\n\n基本的にはウィンドウスコープを使用し、ウィンドウ間でデータを共有する必要がある場合（例えばショッピングカートの商品情報のようにユーザに対して一意である必要があるもの）のみセッションスコープを検討する。 I'm deciding whether to include the introductory paragraph before the first h2 section in s1. Since it contains Layer A content explaining what window scope is and its key capabilities—that it uses hidden tags to maintain data across multiple windows and enables parallel browser windows and history-back navigation—I should fold this into s1 rather than treat it as a separate preamble.\n\nNow I'm structuring the final sections: s1 will combine the intro with the 動作イメージ content, s2 will cover the comparison with session scope, and s3 will contain the detailed information. I'm using the hints to guide what belongs in each section—s1 focuses on window scope mechanics with hidden tags and multi-screen data retention, s2 emphasizes the distinction between scopes and when to use each, and s3 handles the remaining details.\n\nGenerating the JSON structure... I'm structuring the JSON for this window scope learning module, organizing it into three main sections covering the operational overview, comparison with session scope, and detailed implementation information. Now I'm drafting the markdown content for the first section, which explains what window scope is and how it functions. ウィンドウスコープに格納された変数はカスタムタグで自動的にhiddenタグに変換されるため、プログラマが手動でhiddenタグを記述する必要がない。シーケンス図を参照しながら、複数の入力画面でこのデータ引き継ぎがどのように機能するかを確認している。\n\n基本的な設計方針としては、ほとんどのケースではウィンドウスコープを使用してウィンドウ間でのデータ共有を避けるべきだが、ショッピングカート内の商品情報のようにユーザが複数ウィンドウを開いていても単一の状態を保つ必要があるケースではセッションスコープを使用する。\n\nウィンドウスコープの実装方法についてはカスタムタグの実装例を参照する必要があり、相対URLのため公式ドキュメントのURLリストには追加できない。\n\nベースURLが空なので、このリンクはMarkdown形式で保持しつつ、official_doc_urlsは空のままにしておく。\n\nこれでJSONを完成させよう。","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":21239,"cache_read_input_tokens":29955,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":21239,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":8},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"2ebea3be-8867-4c89-a554-b33346c53b01","uuid":"8e23d6fb-3574-48a8-9108-319b13e7d9b8"}
